The paper deals with recommender systems, which are a common application of machine learning. The use of causal inference techniques to handle selection biases is a key aspect of the paper, suggesting that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and recommendation systems, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely category. The use of matrix factorization methods is common in collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of recommender systems, and may suggest cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with practical and scalable methods, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
